            	<p>
						    "Estate" is just a fancy word that means "everything you own" -- home, property, cars, bank accounts, personal possessions, etc... <br>Estate planning essentially means to prepare specific instructions for what will happen to all of your assets in the event of your death or incapacitation.
            	</p>

            	<p>
            		People often think that an estate plan is only necessary later in life, but that is not the case. A properly planned estate is useful at any time, for anyone who wants to control the way their assets are distributed in the event of their death. Developing such a plan is especially important if you have a family, as it is the best way to be sure that everyone will be taken care of.
            	</p>
